.TH "spi_nor_select_uniform_erase" 9 "spi_nor_select_uniform_erase" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
spi_nor_select_uniform_erase \- select optimum uniform erase type
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "const struct spi_nor_erase_type *" spi_nor_select_uniform_erase
.BI "(struct spi_nor_erase_map *map "  ","
.BI "const u32 wanted_size "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "map" 12
the erase map of the SPI NOR
.IP "wanted_size" 12
the erase type size to search for. Contains the value of
info->sector_size or of the "small sector" size in case
CONFIG_MTD_SPI_NOR_USE_4K_SECTORS is defined.
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Once the optimum uniform sector erase command is found, disable all the
other.
.SH "RETURN"
pointer to erase type on success, NULL otherwise.
